{"article_id":"zFgqTI3GAaKFm43b","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"Russia 's Putin 'Probably ' Approved Plan","depth":3},{"id":1,"text":"To Kill Spy ,","depth":3},{"id":2,"text":"British Report Says","depth":2},{"id":3,"text":"Nearly 10 years after Kremlin critic and former spy Alexander Litvinenko was poisoned with a rare radioactive element","depth":7},{"id":4,"text":"and died in London ,","depth":7},{"id":5,"text":"a retired British judge has issued a report","depth":7},{"id":6,"text":"concluding","depth":8},{"id":7,"text":"that Russian President Vladimir Putin `` probably '' approved a plan by Russia 's security service","depth":9},{"id":8,"text":"to kill the former FSB agent .","depth":9},{"id":9,"text":"The Kremlin has long denied any involvement in Litvinenko 's death .","depth":6},{"id":10,"text":"The two men","depth":11},{"id":11,"text":"who are accused of poisoning Litvinenko ,","depth":11},{"id":12,"text":"Andrei Lugovoi and Dmitry Kovtun ,","depth":10},{"id":13,"text":"have suggested","depth":9},{"id":14,"text":"he might have poisoned himself , either intentionally or accidentally .","depth":8},{"id":15,"text":"But the British findings dismiss that possibility , along with the idea","depth":8},{"id":16,"text":"that the situation was some sort of elaborate ruse .","depth":8},{"id":17,"text":"The report","depth":9},{"id":18,"text":"released today by Sir Robert Owen , chairman of the British inquiry into Litvinenko 's murder ,","depth":9},{"id":19,"text":"concludes","depth":8},{"id":20,"text":"that `` the FSB operation","depth":9},{"id":21,"text":"to kill Mr. Litvinenko","depth":9},{"id":22,"text":"was probably approved by Mr. Patrushev , then head of the FSB , and also by President Putin .","depth":8},{"id":23,"text":"Litvinenko 's widow , Marina ,","depth":11},{"id":24,"text":"speaking Thursday outside the Royal Courts of Justice in London ,","depth":11},{"id":25,"text":"welcomed the report","depth":10},{"id":26,"text":"by saying ,","depth":10},{"id":27,"text":"`` The words","depth":12},{"id":28,"text":"my husband spoke on his deathbed ,","depth":13},{"id":29,"text":"when he accused Mr. Putin of his murder ,","depth":13},{"id":30,"text":"have been proved true in an English court . ''","depth":11},{"id":31,"text":"She also urged Prime Minister David Cameron to take action against Putin and Russia .","depth":9},{"id":32,"text":"`` I am calling immediately for the expulsion from the U.K. of all Russian intelligence operatives , ''","depth":11},{"id":33,"text":"Litvinenko said ,","depth":11},{"id":34,"text":"`` whether from the FSB","depth":12},{"id":35,"text":"who murdered Sasha","depth":12},{"id":36,"text":"or from other Russian agencies","depth":12},{"id":37,"text":"based in the London embassy . ''","depth":12},{"id":38,"text":"Responding to the report ,","depth":9},{"id":39,"text":"Russian Foreign Ministry spokesperson Maria Zakharova said ,","depth":10},{"id":40,"text":"`` We regret","depth":11},{"id":41,"text":"that the purely criminal case has been politicized","depth":12},{"id":42,"text":"and has marred the entire atmosphere of bilateral relations . ''","depth":12},{"id":43,"text":"As writer Will Storr told NPR in 2013 ,","depth":9},{"id":44,"text":"`` This has been written about as the first-ever successful nuclear attack on the West by Russia .","depth":10},{"id":45,"text":"It 's a major situation . ''","depth":10},{"id":46,"text":"The report recounts","depth":9},{"id":47,"text":"how the spy came to be in London :","depth":9},{"id":48,"text":"In 2000 , six years before Alexander Litvinenko was poisoned ,","depth":9},{"id":49,"text":"he arrived in the city with his wife and son , Anatoly ,","depth":10},{"id":50,"text":"and made a declaration to a police officer :","depth":11},{"id":51,"text":"`` I am a KGB officer","depth":12},{"id":52,"text":"and I 'm asking for political asylum . ''","depth":12},{"id":53,"text":"Litvinenko was 44","depth":9},{"id":54,"text":"when he died in 2006 of cardiac arrest","depth":10},{"id":55,"text":"brought on by acute radiation syndrome .","depth":10},{"id":56,"text":"The report says","depth":12},{"id":57,"text":"he was poisoned twice -","depth":13},{"id":58,"text":"the first time coming","depth":14},{"id":59,"text":"just days after he and his family were granted British citizenship on Oct. 13 , 2006 .","depth":14},{"id":60,"text":"`` The evidence establishes","depth":13},{"id":61,"text":"that Mr. Litvinenko ingested the fatal dose","depth":14},{"id":62,"text":"whilst drinking tea from a teapot","depth":16},{"id":63,"text":"contaminated with polonium-210 in the Pine Bar of the Millennium Hotel in the West End of London in the afternoon of 1 November in the company of Andrei Lugovoy and Dmitri Kovtun .","depth":16},{"id":64,"text":"I am sure","depth":16},{"id":65,"text":"that Mr. Lugovoy and Mr. Kovtun placed the polonium-210 into the teapot at the Pine Bar","depth":17},{"id":66,"text":"and did so with the intention","depth":18},{"id":67,"text":"of poisoning Mr . Litvinenko . ''","depth":18},{"id":68,"text":"That fatal encounter came","depth":14},{"id":69,"text":"weeks after Lugovoy and Kovtun had attempted to administer polonium-210 to Litvinenko ,","depth":14},{"id":70,"text":"Owen says .","depth":13},{"id":71,"text":"Judge Owen adds","depth":11},{"id":72,"text":"that there 's no sign of a possible personal motive for Lugovoy and Kovtun ,","depth":12},{"id":73,"text":"and that all the evidence in the case `` points in one direction ''","depth":13},{"id":74,"text":"- to Moscow .","depth":13},{"id":75,"text":"Litvinenko died on Nov. 23 , 2006 .","depth":9},{"id":76,"text":"As a former Soviet intelligence officer wrote for The Telegraph in 2009 ,","depth":7},{"id":77,"text":"Litvinenko 's clashes with Putin extend at least back to 1998 ,","depth":8},{"id":78,"text":"when he blew the whistle on orders from the FSB","depth":10},{"id":79,"text":"to murder a politician in Russia .","depth":10},{"id":80,"text":"At the time , Putin had been in charge of the FSB for a matter of months ;","depth":10},{"id":81,"text":"Litvinenko was arrested and placed under scrutiny","depth":11},{"id":82,"text":"until he managed to reach London .","depth":11},{"id":83,"text":"The material","depth":7},{"id":84,"text":"that killed Litvinenko","depth":7},{"id":85,"text":"has a half-life of just 138 days ;","depth":6},{"id":86,"text":"it also leaves a faint blue glow","depth":6},{"id":87,"text":"that helped forensic investigators track the polonium-210 's trail through London .","depth":6},{"id":88,"text":"As for the alleged perpetrators , the report states ,","depth":6},{"id":89,"text":"`` Warrants were in due course issued for their arrest ,","depth":7},{"id":90,"text":"and the Crown Prosecution Service sought unsuccessfully to extradite them from the Russian Federation","depth":8},{"id":91,"text":"to stand trial for murder . ''","depth":8},{"id":92,"text":"The report had been delayed by several factors , from the complicated nature of the police investigation to frustrated attempts","depth":6},{"id":93,"text":"to question ,","depth":8},{"id":94,"text":"and perhaps prosecute ,","depth":8},{"id":95,"text":"the Russian men","depth":8},{"id":96,"text":"who are accused of carrying out the order .","depth":8},{"id":97,"text":"Owen was appointed to the case in August of 2012 .","depth":2}],"relations":[{"parent":195,"left":100,"right":194,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":100,"left":99,"right":2,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":99,"left":0,"right":1,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":194,"left":193,"right":97,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":193,"left":179,"right":192,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":179,"left":113,"right":178,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":113,"left":105,"right":112,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":105,"left":101,"right":104,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":101,"left":3,"right